Stop Stage Fright in 10 seconds!

New FREE Resource: The FBI Reset Toolkit: a Downloadable Backstage Companion for Performers from Beyond The Spotlight Psychology.

For performers, the moments right before stepping on stage are often the most vulnerable.

Warm-ups can fade, techniques can slip and anxiety takes the spotlight.

That‚Äôs why I‚Äôve packaged the FBI Reset into a portable, backstage-ready toolkit you can download and keep on your phone.

What‚Äôs inside the free toolkit:

üéß Downloadable Audio Guide: A clean, FBI Reset audio track (F=Feet, B=Breath, I=Intention) enhanced with calming music - ready to use offline, anytime nerves strike.

üìò Companion PDF Guide: A detailed walkthrough of the science and a practice protocol to integrate the reset into your pre-show routine.

üéØ Exclusive Bonus: The Stage Fright Symptom Profiler - a diagnostic tool to help you identify your unique anxiety patterns and tailor your coping strategies.

I am really passionate about giving all of you - stage performing artists a clinical tool in your pocket when you need it most.

It is perfect for musicians, singers, actors, speakers, and anyone who faces performance pressure.

‚¨áÔ∏è Download your free copy here https://www.beyondthespotlightpsychology.co.uk/freebie-stage-profiler-sign-up-page

I‚Äôd love to hear how it works for you backstage.

Feel free to share with colleagues who may benefit from it. Thank you.

Dr Maja Jankowska, Clinical & Counselling Psychologist

Beyond The Spotlight Psychology

items.text: Hi I have a 17 year old daughter who it‚Äôs heart set on studying musical theatre at degree level. We are based in Northern Ireland but she ideally wants to be in London or near there. I have been exploring this and the costs seem extortionate! We cannot as a family afford to contribute. We earn just above the threshold of lower income so not rich but not poor enough for lots of the bursaries etc. Are families like ours just priced out of the industry? Are there any threads, pages etc that parents can chat to each other about this type of thing? My daughter is very capable and I really want to support her but in reality we will struggle and potentially sink in the process!

topComments.text: My daughters at the hammond in chester lots of students there from Ireland a fantastic dance and drama school ! They fly into Liverpool or ferry over

Could you rent her bedroom out to a lodger (which the lodger pays direct to daughter so it doesn‚Äôt impact your earnings) and negotiate with college that she will pay any top up fees monthly from the lodgers rent? This has got my daughter through Arts Ed. 

She had to live in a tiny box room for her first and second year, bed up a ladder, boxes and desk underneath, allowing her to pay a reduced share of rent. 

She has worked Saturdays and Sundays for three years to help with travel and food that her maintenance grant just didn‚Äôt stretch to with London rents to pay, which was exhausting but it‚Äôs the only way we could make it work. 

Christmas and Birthdays are opportunities to buy kit and things they really need. 

Once they are at the colleges there are also other opportunities to audition for and be recommended for other funding bursaries. 

My daughter also wrote at least three letters a week to charity giving bodies and trusts giving them an overview of who she is and what she is training in with a clear budget of her outgoings that she is fundraising for and she has been very fortunate to receive financial help that way too. 

Create the opportunities, plan well, budget realistically, and ALWAYS have enough in the pot that if she NEEDS to, she can fly home for a weekend when the going gets really tough and she just needs a Mummy cuddle and a home cooked meal. Even if she does have to sleep on the sofa‚Ä¶ üòä - the students who are far away from
home and can‚Äôt get back find it extra hard, so if you can have that in your back pocket and only use it when really needed.

items.text: My son 17 is looking to increase his experience could anyone point me in the right direction for helping him reach his dreams? Any advice greatly appreciated x

topComments.text: Your post is very vague. How old is your son. Does he have an agent and are you able to travel to castings/jobs. If he is under 18 you need to be very careful what advice you take and from whom. There are a couple of large parents groups for child actors but that won‚Äôt be relevant if he is over 18.

Get him enrolled in a local taught drama group...not amdram....but a place where he is taught to act.  If he has talent get him to drama school....learn the craft, then get representation.  Its also important to consider what type of acting....different schools specialise in different elements.  Some feed to soap operas, some specialise in dance, singing and acting, some only do acting, some do fight work.  

So it all depends what he wants to do....but it all begins with learning the craft of acting.

items.text:
Hello! My name is Philip √ì hAodha, and I‚Äôm looking for someone to help co-host my multistream live chats on YouTube, TikTok, Twitch, and Instagram.
I use a multistream setup, so you can connect all of your social media platforms as well. I run the live streams, but I often get a lot of people joining at once, and trying to read questions, answer them, and stay entertaining all at the same time can get overwhelming. I‚Äôd love someone to jump in and give me a hand.

I‚Äôm especially interested in young people who want experience in hosting and helping out on live streams. My platforms focus on Irish medieval history, but no history experience is needed.

All I‚Äôm looking for is someone who can:

Read and manage questions

Be creative, fun, and engaging

Help keep the chat flowing

If you‚Äôre interested, comment below or message me on Facebook or Instagram.

We are casting actors for an IN-PERSON table read in Los Angeles of my upcoming short film, "How Much For the Night?" This table read will be recorded. 

Please submit headshot and *reel to bookings@fathajazz.com for further consideration. An NDA and sides will be sent to all eligible submissions for self tapes. 

*Reels are strongly preferred, but not required.

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text

May be a graphic of text that says 'o Much For The Night?" LOGLINE When an ambitious, black rideshare driver sets out on her routine shift and accepts a ride for 3 suburban white women headed to an event in a small, rural town, she is not prepared for the cross-cultural chaos that ensues. PLEASE SUBMIT YOUR HEADSHOT & *REEL to bookings@fathajazz.com bookings'

May be a graphic of text that says 'WE ARE IN THE FINAL STAGES OF DEVELOPMENT FOR THIS PROJECT AND WILL BE USING THIS TABLE READ TO FINALIZE THE SCRIPT. ALL ACTORS MAY HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY To REPRISE THEIR ROLE IN THE FILMIF IF THEY ARE A GOOD FIT. *ACTING REEL PREFERRED, BUT NOT REQUIRED AT THIS STAGE.'

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM (LONDON)
Project Type: Independent Feature Film
Genre: Drama
Location: London, UK
Language: English
Status: Casting main and supporting roles

items.text:
Hello everyone! I'm looking for someone who is Cornwall-based to star in my 3rd-year graduate short film in partnership with Falmouth University, called Two Lips and Daisies.

Two Lips and Daisies is a 10-minute short rom-com about a ¬£40k orchid, a furious florist and a wedding gone completely off the rails! The character that i'm looking to cast is the role of Donny Two Lips who is an older man with enormous lips who speaks with a cockney accent with a personality and witty British humour to match!

Synopsis: 
* When a penny-pinching mother-of-the-bride accidentally walks out of a flower shop with a 40 grand orchid instead of tulips, her daughter‚Äôs wedding spirals into chaos. Seeing everything unfold, the underdog groom seizes the opportunity to stand up to his overbearing mother-in-law and put her in her place, revealing her true colours to everyone. Proving that true love is worth more than some soppy orchids.‚Äã

Donny Two Lips (50s)

Donny works at a local florist down the road when he loses his precious ¬£40k orchid due to a mix-up. This causes him to do anything in his power to get them back, even if that means turning up to the wedding himself. He loves to swear and use witty insults on anyone he encounters. Imagine him as a character from Snatch but thrown into a world in which he doesn't really belong, elevating the surreal humour that this story carries!

Shooting Dates and Compensation:

22nd February & 2-4 March, all in Falmouth and Truro, Cornwall. travel and food expenses will be covered on set, and pay is negotiable between myself and my producer!

Final Details:

If you have any questions about the production or compensation or would like the script, then please get in contact with me either through here or via my email, which is TL298912@Falmouth.ac.uk

Tristan ~ Writer/Director for Two Lips and Daisies

items.text:
GODSPELL ‚Äî VIDEO AUDITIONS

Wedgwood Arts

Wedgwood Arts is pleased to announce video auditions for Godspell! This non-paid production will be joyful, ensemble-driven, and thoughtfully crafted. We are seeking performers who value storytelling, collaboration, and making meaningful theatre together.

The Production team for Godspell:
Director: A. Solomon Abah Jr.
Music Direction: Adam Frame
Choreographer: (TBA) 
Stage Manager: (TBA)

PERFORMANCE DATES

April 17‚Äì19

AUDITION SUBMISSION DETAILS

Audition Deadline: Saturday, February 7 at 11:59pm
Callbacks: Monday, February 9 at St. Matthew‚Äôs Lutheran Church
 5709 Wedgwood Dr. Fort Worth, TX. 76133

Where to Send Auditions
wedgwoodarts@gmail.com

Email Subject Line
Godspell Audition ‚Äì [Your Name]

WHAT TO SUBMIT
1. Vocal Selection

‚Ä¢ One song, 60‚Äì90 seconds
‚Ä¢ Musical theatre or contemporary style preferred
‚Ä¢ Focus on clear text, musical accuracy, and connection
‚Ä¢ Recorded accompaniment, live accompaniment, or a cappella are all acceptable
‚Ä¢ Singing from Godspell is welcome but not required

2. Audition Side
The following Audition side has 3 parts a Narrot, a father, and a son. Have fun and show us different choices for each voice. We are excited to see your personality, sincerity, and ease with an audience.:

The son ran to meet his father, threw his arms around him, and kissed him, saying: ‚ÄúFather, I have sinned against God and against you; I am no longer fit to be called your son; treat me as one of your paid servants.‚Äù But the father called to one of his servants: ‚ÄúQuick, fetch me my robe, my best one. Put a ring on his finger and shoes on his feet and bring the fatted calf and kill it. And let us have a feast to celebrate the day, for this son of mine was lost and is found.‚Äù And the festivities began!

3. Movement

‚Ä¢ 20‚Äì30 seconds of simple movement
‚Ä¢ Movement to music or light choreography is welcome
‚Ä¢ No dance experience required‚Äîcomfort, rhythm, and willingness to move are what matter most

4. Slate (At the Beginning of Your Video)

Please include:
‚Ä¢ Your name
‚Ä¢ Pronouns (optional)
‚Ä¢ Age range
‚Ä¢ Vocal range (if known)
‚Ä¢ Any instruments you play (if applicable)

5. Video Guidelines

‚Ä¢ One video or multiple videos are fine
‚Ä¢ Phone recordings are perfectly acceptable
‚Ä¢ Neutral background and good lighting recommended
‚Ä¢ Please record each section in one continuous take

6. IN THE EMAIL BODY

First and last name 
Phone number 
Email 
Which parts you are willing to accept 
Any rehearsal conflicts 

REHEARSAL COMMITMENT

Rehearsals begin Monday, February 16 and will be held on Monday and Thursday nights from 7:00‚Äì10:00 PM and Saturdays from 10:00-1:00. 

This process will move intentionally and efficiently from the start, allowing us to create a polished, cohesive production while still building strong ensemble connections. Consistent attendance, preparation, and collaboration are essential.

Tech Week: April 12‚Äì14
Dress Rehearsal: April 16
Performances: April 17‚Äì19

Please audition only if you are able to commit to this schedule.

Godspell is a show rooted in generosity, joy, and shared responsibility. We are eager to bring together a company excited to do focused, meaningful work.

We look forward to seeing your auditions.

ROLES
We are looking for a diverse cast for this show. Performers of any ethnicity, race, color, sex, gender, age, sexual orientation, religion will be considered for the show. 
Jesus: The spiritual and emotional center of the piece. Warm, charismatic, and deeply grounded, with the ability to lead the ensemble through storytelling rather than authority. Strong singer with a gentle, confident presence. 
John the Baptist/Judas: A dual role. John the Baptist opens the show with joyful energy and clarity; Judas evolves into a conflicted, questioning figure. Requires emotional depth, strong acting skills, and vocal diversity. 
We are looking for 8 Actors who fill the following descriptions 
Performer 1: Energetic, playful, and physically expressive. Often drives movement-based storytelling and comic moments. Strong ensemble singer with confidence in unaccompanied sections. 
Performer 2: Bold, charismatic, and impulsive. Often delivers comedic text with sharp timing and physicality. Strong pop/rock vocal presence. 
Performer 3: Thoughtful, gentle, and reflective. Often anchors quieter moments and parables. Warm vocal tone and emotional sincerity. 
Performer 4: Expressive and emotionally open. Often carries lyrical and heartfelt material. Strong singer with the ability to communicate vulnerability. 
Performer 5: Bright, optimistic, and sincere. Frequently leads joyful or playful moments in the ensemble. Clear tone and strong blend. 
Performer 6: Quirky, imaginative, and playful. Comfortable with character work, storytelling, and musical humor. 
Performer 7: Grounded, mature, and emotionally resonant. Often supports dramatic moments with calm authority. Strong musicianship required. 
Performer 8: Confident, dynamic, and expressive. Often takes leadership within group numbers and physical storytelling. Strong rhythmic feel and vocal power.

‚Ä¢ Vocal range (if known)
‚Ä¢ Any instruments you play (if applicable)

5. Video Guidelines

‚Ä¢ One video or multiple videos are fine
‚Ä¢ Phone recordings are perfectly acceptable
‚Ä¢ Neutral background and good lighting recommended
‚Ä¢ Please record each section in one continuous take

6. IN THE EMAIL BODY

First and last name 
Phone number 
Email 
Which parts you are willing to accept 
Any rehearsal conflicts 

REHEARSAL COMMITMENT

Rehearsals begin Monday, February 16 and will be held on Monday and Thursday nights from 7:00‚Äì10:00 PM and Saturdays from 10:00-1:00. 

This process will move intentionally and efficiently from the start, allowing us to create a polished, cohesive production while still building strong ensemble connections. Consistent attendance, preparation, and collaboration are essential.

Tech Week: April 12‚Äì14
Dress Rehearsal: April 16
Performances: April 17‚Äì19

Please audition only if you are able to commit to this schedule.

Godspell is a show rooted in generosity, joy, and shared responsibility. We are eager to bring together a company excited to do focused, meaningful work.

We look forward to seeing your auditions.

ROLES
We are looking for a diverse cast for this show. Performers of any ethnicity, race, color, sex, gender, age, sexual orientation, religion will be considered for the show. 
Jesus: The spiritual and emotional center of the piece. Warm, charismatic, and deeply grounded, with the ability to lead the ensemble through storytelling rather than authority. Strong singer with a gentle, confident presence. 
John the Baptist/Judas: A dual role. John the Baptist opens the show with joyful energy and clarity; Judas evolves into a conflicted, questioning figure. Requires emotional depth, strong acting skills, and vocal diversity. 
We are looking for 8 Actors who fill the following descriptions 
Performer 1: Energetic, playful, and physically expressive. Often drives movement-based storytelling and comic moments. Strong ensemble singer with confidence in unaccompanied sections. 
Performer 2: Bold, charismatic, and impulsive. Often delivers comedic text with sharp timing and physicality. Strong pop/rock vocal presence. 
Performer 3: Thoughtful, gentle, and reflective. Often anchors quieter moments and parables. Warm vocal tone and emotional sincerity. 
Performer 4: Expressive and emotionally open. Often carries lyrical and heartfelt material. Strong singer with the ability to communicate vulnerability. 
Performer 5: Bright, optimistic, and sincere. Frequently leads joyful or playful moments in the ensemble. Clear tone and strong blend. 
Performer 6: Quirky, imaginative, and playful. Comfortable with character work, storytelling, and musical humor. 
Performer 7: Grounded, mature, and emotionally resonant. Often supports dramatic moments with calm authority. Strong musicianship required. 
Performer 8: Confident, dynamic, and expressive. Often takes leadership within group numbers and physical storytelling. Strong rhythmic feel and vocal power.

Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.

> 

Skuespillere i alderen 16-24 √•r samt 30-50 √•r (b√•de m/k) i Aalborg s√∏ges til film for sorgramte unge p√• erhvervsuddannelser üé•

**Hvorn√•r:**

Vi optager nu p√• torsdag og fredag d. 22 og 23. januar i den kommende uge (uge 4) Opgaven er ul√∏nnet, men **transportudgifter** **d√¶kkes** og der vil v√¶re **forplejning p√• set**. 

Kunne du t√¶nke dig at hj√¶lpe med at formidle vigtige budskaber for ansatte og unge p√• erhvervsuddannelser samt f√• erfaring med at v√¶re foran kameraet, s√• l√¶s videre!

**Om kampagnen:**

Vi s√∏ger skuespillere til optagelse af nogle korte scener p√• **Aalborg TechCollege**, n√•r **Det Nationale Sorgcenter **skal producere en r√¶kke film til kompetenceudvikling i h√•ndtering af sorg for p√•r√∏rende. 

**Optagelser varer ca. 2 timer **og involverer skuespil ud fra et mindre manuskript.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Diaspora

We are casting for a short narrative film titled Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Diaspora is set in 1970s Britain and follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport, whose encounter with a Balkan-born photographer leads both men to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. Set largely within a photography studio, the film is intimate and character-driven, relying on subtle performance, quiet tension, and emotional restraint.

This is an intimate short film exploring displacement, identity in transition, and the unspoken grief carried by those who leave their homeland. 

Filming will take place in Bristol and surrounding areas in early March (exact dates TBC). This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided. The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

We are looking for performers who feel natural, emotionally grounded, and sensitive to character, with the ability to convey internal states through stillness and small gestures.

To apply:ÔøΩPlease send a headshot and CV to diasporafilm2026@gmail.com

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are January 22 to February 6, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì PAID, NON-UNION COMMERCIAL**

Novel Productions is casting **two roles** for a **35-second commercial** for VWR Capital Corp.

**Shoot Location:** Vancouver, BC
**Shoot Date:** January 23, 2026 (8 Hours)
**Compensation:** $300 (non-union)

**ROLES:**
‚Ä¢ **The Broker** ‚Äî Age **25‚Äì35** | Gender & ethnicity open
‚Ä¢ **The VWR Rep** ‚Äî Age **35‚Äì55** | Gender & ethnicity open

**SUBMISSIONS:**
Please send **headshot, acting resume, and reel (if available)** to: **info@novelproductions.ca**

**Subject line:**
*VWR Casting - Role Name - Your Name*

Selected submissions will be contacted with sides and instructions for self-tape auditions.

Nocturne are seeking a synth and keyboard player to join an established progressive theatrical metal band with influences of Black Sabbath, Tool and Opeth. 

We have a clear artistic vision rooted in old school prog metal, drawing keyboard and synth influence from Genesis, Ghost, Rush, and Dream Theater. We are looking for someone who can fit within an existing sound and aesthetic, while also bringing their own musical voice.

Rehearsals are Liverpool and Manchester based. This is a committed, serious project with live performance at its core.

Live performance experience necessary.
Comfortable performing in costume and character.
Backing vocals wanted but not essential.

To apply, please email nocturnebanduk@gmail.com or fill in the form linked in our bio.
Include a short video that best represents your playing style.

#progmetal #synthplayer #liverpool #liverpoolmusic #progrock

**Casting Call - 1970s Biographical Feature Film**

For a new biographical feature film set in the 1970s, we are looking for **MEN aged approx. 20-35, up to 180 cm max., **an athletic build. In role** future MILITARY PERSONNEL**.

Gentlemen of the following origins are particularly welcome:
* **CUBANS**
* **MONGOLIANS**
* **BULGARIANS**
* **HULGARIANS**

**Shooting Days:**
* February 5 ‚Äì shooting in Warsaw
* March 18 ‚Äì shooting in Warsaw
* March 26 ‚Äì shooting in Pi≈Ça (transport and hotel provided)
* May 1 ‚Äì shooting likely in Warsaw (TBC)

**Rate: 450 PLN per shooting day**

**Characterization Guidelines:**
* Absolutely no tattoos
* Hair must be short, but cut without the use of clippers
* No facial hair (clean-shaven)
* Athletic build

**Please send applications to:** **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**
**Subject Line:** **KKZ**
**Email Content:** Name and surname, age, phone number, city/town of residence, nationality + measurements: height, chest, waist, hips, clothing and shoe size.
**Attachment:** **PHOTO OF FACE AND FIGURE: taken only on the day of application + profile photo**

**FACE PHOTO** ‚Äì portrait selfie in daylight, straight-on, looking into the lens. No filters. No glasses. No head covering.
**FIGURE PHOTO** ‚Äì in clothing that shows the outline of the figure.

If you‚Äôre doing a live callback online, always prep first.
Remember, first impressions count.

Before you go live do some prep !

1.Check the space and background you‚Äôre in to make sure it is clean, neutral, and distraction free

2.Test the lighting so your face is clearly lit

3.Test the sound to ensure it is clear with no echo or background noise

4.Check your internet connection

A few minutes of prep can be the difference between a smooth, confident callback and avoidable stress.

#marksummerscasting #marksummers #castingdirector #callbacks

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Diaspora

We are casting for a short narrative film titled Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Diaspora is set in 1970s Britain and follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport, whose encounter with a Balkan-born photographer leads both men to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. Set largely within a photography studio, the film is intimate and character-driven, relying on subtle performance, quiet tension, and emotional restraint.

This is an intimate short film exploring displacement, identity in transition, and the unspoken grief carried by those who leave their homeland. 

Filming will take place in Bristol and surrounding areas in early March (exact dates TBC). This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided. The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

We are looking for performers who feel natural, emotionally grounded, and sensitive to character, with the ability to convey internal states through stillness and small gestures.

To apply:ÔøΩPlease send a headshot and CV to diasporafilm2026@gmail.com

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'Diaspora Britain, immigrant Balkan photographer form an unexpected bond during passport photo session, confronting memories migration, and the ache of living between two homes. Roles ALI: casting for: young Cypriot applying for British passport. tries stay in control, but flashes of memory expose unresolved displacement and doubt about where he belongs. THE PHOTOGRAPHER: Male, late A who fled his homeland years ago. Emotionally guarded, keeps clients distance until he recognises something familiar Ali's struggle. To apply, send headshots & CV's to dliasporaim2026agrmail.com Filming Bristol Surrounding areas Early March dates TBC. Seeking contributors travel expenses and food will be provided.'

items.text:
Hi, there! My name is Zo√´ - I'm an American actor living in Edinburgh, and I am beginning to offer private individual or group acting coaching sessions. I graduated with my MFA degree in Acting for the Stage and Screen last year, and before moving to Scotland, I lived in Los Angeles, CA for 7 years, where I earned my Bachelor of Arts degree in Acting. I've been acting for almost 20 years now and have studied at the University of Southern California's School of Dramatic Arts (LA), The National Theatre Institute (CT & UK), The Storyteller's Conservatory (LA), The Actor's Gym (NYC), and Edinburgh Napier University. 

I have a strong and extensive background on both stage and screen, and I'm keen to work with individuals who are looking to develop their audition technique. I have years of experience working alongside other actors on self tapes and stage auditions, and I have developed a personal group of friends who come to me for help with auditions. My experience and confidence working with friends has inspired me to try to help others. 

If you or anyone you know might be interested, please feel free to send me a DM. I am open to working with people online or in person, and I'm happy to offer one-off sessions or consistent sessions. 

For samples of my own acting work, including my showreel and voice over reels, you can view my Spotlight profile here: https://app.spotlight.com/5816-4509-4543

Additionally, I have just launched my own production company last year with my partner. It's called Muddrag Productions, and I am producing, directing, and starring in our first project currently in development. My experience working as a director for both the stage and screen has bolstered my ability to help other actors from a different perspective, understanding, and expectation.

Looking forward to hearing from you!

Best,

Zo√´

items.text:
Hinweis zur Schauspiel- & Komparsenkartei
Vielen Dank f√ºr das aktuell sehr gro√üe Interesse an der Schauspiel- & Komparsenkartei von KiliaanFilms.

Aufgrund der hohen Nachfrage ist das Aufnahmeformular derzeit vor√ºbergehend geschlossen, damit alle bereits eingegangenen Bewerbungen sorgf√§ltig bearbeitet werden k√∂nnen.

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

# **VI S√òGER STATISTER **

Vi s√∏ger featured statister M/K/NB i alderen 28-45 til en kortfilm af Agnes Trier. Castet inkluderer Filippa Coster-Waldau, Jacob Lohmann, Olivia Joof, Sidsel Siem Koch og Kitt Maiken Mortensen. 

Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.

Tristans mor er en karakterunders√∏gelse af en ung kvinde i en s√•rbar periode.

Praktisk info:

Du skal spille en for√¶ldre i for√¶ldregruppen, s√• det vigtigt du kan deltage i optagelser hele dagen d. 24/1+25/1 i tidsrummet 8-18, og meget gerne ogs√• en halv dag i aftentimerne mandag. d. 26/1.

Erfaring med improvisation og replikker er en fordel, men ikke et 

krav.

Jobbet er ul√∏nnet men vi s√∏ger for forplejning og god energi. 

Vi filmer i Sydhavnen.

Ved interesse send vellignende billede, samt navn, alder og erfaring til casting@adomeitfilm.com

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races and ethnicities are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

If you‚Äôd like to participate, please comment below and let me know!

To effectively show off all the site's capabilities, we need users to complete **100% of their profiles.** 

If you're not interested in being showcased but still want to explore the site, you can check us out at [www.castingly.com](http://www.castingly.com/). 

**Membership is free through 2026!** We'll also be rolling out casting breakdowns within the next few weeks. Feel free to reach out if you have any questions!

items.text:
# **Casting Call ‚Äì Vancouver Laser & Skin Care Centre**

Hi everyone!
We are currently casting talent for **vertical ads **to promote our upcoming **February & March campaign**.

## **Roles Needed**
* **2 talents (male & female)**
* **Age:** 25‚Äì35
* **Ethnicity:** Caucasian or East Asian
* **Language:** Native-level English fluency
* **Preferred (not required):** Experience with social media content, beauty industry, or ad shoots

##  **Project Details**
* **Deliverables:** 6‚Äì9 vertical videos (approx. 15-second ads)
* **Shoot Duration:** 3.5‚Äì4 hours (approx.)
* **Shoot Date:** 
For the **February Shooting**: One day between **January 21-23** (exact date TBC)
For the **March Shooting**: One day between **February 16-25** (exact date TBC)
* **Location**: 750 W Broadway 3rd Floor, Vancouver, BC V5Z 1H2
* **Wardrobe & Makeup:** Not provided ‚Äî please dress in **business-casual style**

##  **Compensation**
* **$300 flat rate**
* **One BBL or PicoWay Treatment**
* **Snacks & coffee provided** 

## **How to Apply**

Please email the following to **ben@vancouverlaser.com**
**Subject line:** *February/March Campaign + [Your Name]*
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo videos (if available)

**Please note that private messages will not be replied to**.

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out.
We look forward to your submissions!

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì AMBER (LEAD ROLE)**

**Short Film | Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller**

Hello everyone,

We‚Äôre reopening casting for the **lead role of Amber** due to an unexpected last-minute change. The actress previously cast had to step away for a paid commitment. There are no hard feelings ‚Äî we completely understand and wish her the best. This does, however, mean we‚Äôre reaching out again in hopes of finding the right person to step in and collaborate with us.
**PROJECT DETAILS**

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Date:** **Sunday, January 18th**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

All preparation is already in place. If you‚Äôre available and able to step in, you would genuinely be **saving the day** and helping us keep the shoot on track.
**ROLE: AMBER**

**Age Range:** 27‚Äì40
**Gender:** Female
**Ethnicity:** Open / Race-agnostic
**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she begins to rely on it too heavily. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.
**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a **subtle, internal performance**. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and a loss of trust in her own judgment.
**KEY TRAITS**
* Intelligent
* Controlled
* Ambitious (not arrogant)
* Emotionally guarded
* Increasingly detached
**AUDITION / SUBMISSION**

Self-tape audition
One dramatic scene (sides will be provided)

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)

**Email:** soultales.ca@gmail.com
**Subject:** AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

Experience the Demidov Acting Technique at our Demidov One Day Introductory Intensive happening Tuesday April 21st 2026 from 10am-4pm at Pushkin House in London!

This One Day Intensive Workshop is an ideal introduction to the Demidov Acting Technique, and a chance to go deeper into the work for actors familiar with the work.

During this intensive, you will be introduced to Demidov‚Äôs Culture of Creative Freedom, at the root of the Demidov Organic Acting Technique, which sets it apart from other techniques and approaches to acting.  You will be introduced to Demidov‚Äôs signature etudes (improvisational exercises with a given text). 

Through Demidov‚Äôs etudes we get a first taste of what it means to truly live in the moment, to truly see and hear on stage, to remain ‚Äòhere and now‚Äô. We are encouraged to trust our spontaneous urges, and exercise creative freedom. We do so by surrendering to the genuine life that develops on its own.

Click the link üîó below to read more and email us at office@demidovstudiolondon.com with any questions!

https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/courses/demidov-one-day-introductory-intensive-april26

Located at Pushkin House, 5a Bloomsbury Square, London WC1A 2TA

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

items.text:
Hey everyone!

We are now casting **non-union actors** for *An Empty Cup*, a satirical dramedy student short film supported by Vancouver Film School.

This is a **student-led, non-union volunteer production**. While unpaid, the project includes full craft services, catering, and a complimentary professional headshot session for selected performers.

Self-tape submissions open **January 14 at 9:00 AM** and close **January 24 at 11:00 PM**. In-person callbacks will be held on **January 26 from 12:00 PM to 4:00 PM**.

Filming is scheduled for **February 7‚Äì8, 2026** in the **Greater Vancouver Area**.

We are seeking talent for multiple roles with **open ethnicity casting** and encourage performers of all backgrounds to submit. Below, the synopsis of the film and roles of each character are posted.

For more information, please visit our Instagram (@anemptycup_film) or email us at anemptycupfilm@gmail.com.

-An Empty Cup Crew

Synopsis:

16 year old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

manipulated by an unseen presence. When his best friend Sam (16) turns up on New Year‚Äôs Eve, Noah finds himself caught between feelings he‚Äôs long buried and the Voice that refuses to let him go.

SAM (Actor 16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Warm, intuitive, and grounded. Noah‚Äôs best friend; emotionally open, present, and deeply human.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Diaspora

We are casting for a short narrative film titled Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Diaspora is set in 1970s Britain and follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport, whose encounter with a Balkan-born photographer leads both men to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. Set largely within a photography studio, the film is intimate and character-driven, relying on subtle performance, quiet tension, and emotional restraint.

This is an intimate short film exploring displacement, identity in transition, and the unspoken grief carried by those who leave their homeland. 

Filming will take place in Bristol and surrounding areas in early March (exact dates TBC). This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided. The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

We are looking for performers who feel natural, emotionally grounded, and sensitive to character, with the ability to convey internal states through stillness and small gestures.

To apply:ÔøΩPlease send a headshot and CV to diasporafilm2026@gmail.com

THE PHOTOGRAPHER: Male, late A who fled his homeland years ago. Emotionally guarded, keeps clients distance until he recognises something familiar Ali's struggle. To apply, send headshots & CV's to dliasporaim2026agrmail.com Filming Bristol Surrounding areas Early March dates TBC. Seeking contributors travel expenses and food will be provided.'

Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: ‚ÄúThe Balled of Crooked Lane‚Äù by Tom Mclennan and ‚ÄúWake‚Äù by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
‚ÄúThe Ballad of Crooked Lane‚Äù is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

‚ÄúWake‚Äù When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.
